quote: To win here again means everything. The course is tough, the competition was fierce, and to come through in that sprint was a huge team effort — GIANT Australia delivered when it mattered.
A nice way to enter the off season
Time to have a crack, not a racer but the lure of qualification for next yrs UCI Gravel Worlds in WA Australia I thought why NOT. Perfect conditions at the start but an hr in it all changed.
Stunning gravel roads meander through thickly forested valleys, tilt skywards over the hills of the High country and undulate across farmlands and ridgelines.
Seymour — thank you. Again. You may have soaked us to the bone, but your warmth shone through. Even drenched, your gravel remains world-class.
